cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CC

The paper deals with the problem of secure communication in a wireline network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The presence of a passive external adversary also suggests a focus on cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the design and analysis of secure transmission schemes, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI) and computer communication (cs.CC).
